</style>

<section class="rv-faq">
  <div class="rv-faq-container">

    <p class="rv-faq-eyebrow">Rooted Veda</p>
    <h1 class="rv-faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p class="rv-faq-subtitle">Everything you need to know about Nature's Botox and the ancient wisdom behind it.</p>

    <!-- CATEGORY 1 -->
    <div class="rv-faq-category">
      <h2 class="rv-faq-category-title">Ayurveda &amp; Your Skin</h2>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">What makes this "Nature's Botox"?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p>Traditional Botox works by <strong>freezing muscles</strong> by injection. Our Ayurvedic oil works by <strong>revitalizing them</strong> using a blend of "The Four Core."</p>
            <div class="ingredient-grid">
              <div class="ingredient-card"><strong>Organic Jojoba</strong>To balance — mimics natural sebum to balance oil production.</div>
              <div class="ingredient-card"><strong>Organic Almond</strong>To glow — brightens complexion and fades dark spots.</div>
              <div class="ingredient-card"><strong>Organic Castor</strong>To plump — plumps deep tissues and stimulates collagen.</div>
              <div class="ingredient-card"><strong>Organic Frankincense</strong>To lift — tightens pores and speeds up cell renewal.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">The Core Four: What does each ingredient actually do?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p><strong>1. Jojoba Oil — The Balancer</strong><br>In Ayurveda, Jojoba is known for its Tridoshic nature. Its molecular structure is nearly identical to human sebum. It acts as a "smart" oil — dissolving congestion in oily (Kapha) skin, while providing a protective barrier for dry (Vata) skin. It ensures the formula is delivered deep into the dermis without leaving a greasy residue.</p>
            <p><strong>2. Sweet Almond Oil — The Nourisher</strong><br>Referred to as <em>Badam Taila</em> in Ayurveda, it is rich in Vitamins E and A and prized for its oleation properties. It softens skin, fades dark spots and under-eye circles, and is especially grounding for Vata types who struggle with fine lines.</p>
            <p><strong>3. Castor Oil — The Renewer</strong><br>Traditionally used as a "Srotas" channel cleanser. It contains ricinoleic acid, which pulls moisture into the skin, providing the physical plumping effect that fills in deep-set wrinkles and stimulates production of collagen and elastin.</p>
            <p><strong>4. Frankincense Essential Oil — The Sacred Healer</strong><br>Known as <em>Boswellia</em>, used for millennia in sacred rituals. It is a natural astringent that tightens and lifts the skin, speeds up skin cell rejuvenation, and acts as a powerful anti-inflammatory for sensitive (Pitta) skin — reducing redness and smoothing texture.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">Is this oil safe for my skin type?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p>Yes. Nature's Botox is formulated to be <strong>Tridoshic</strong> — carefully balanced for all three Doshas and safe for every skin type. Because we use 100% pure, organic, cold-pressed oils with zero synthetic fragrances or harsh preservatives, our formula is particularly gentle on sensitive skin.</p>
            <div class="dosha-grid">
              <div class="dosha-card"><strong>Vata / Dry</strong>Provides deep, grounding hydration and elasticity.</div>
              <div class="dosha-card"><strong>Pitta / Sensitive</strong>Naturally cooling botanicals soothe redness and calm irritation.</div>
              <div class="dosha-card"><strong>Kapha / Oily</strong>Lightweight, non-comedogenic oils balance sebum without clogging pores.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">Sensitive Skin Transition Guide — how do I start?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p>Switching to a 100% pure botanical ritual is a beautiful gift for sensitive skin. Follow this 3-step introduction for your most comfortable glow yet.</p>
            <div class="step-block"><strong>Step 1 — The Patch Test (First 24 Hours)</strong>Apply 1 drop to the inside of your wrist or behind your ear. Wait 24 hours to ensure your skin is ready for the high-potency Frankincense and Castor oils.</div>
            <div class="step-block"><strong>Step 2 — The "Damp Skin" Rule</strong>Never apply to bone-dry skin. Mist your face with pure water or rose hydrosol first, then press 2 drops into your palms and gently pat onto your face. The water acts as a carrier, helping the oil absorb faster.</div>
            <div class="step-block"><strong>Step 3 — Ease In</strong>Days 1–3: Apply once a day (preferably at night). Day 4+: Once your skin feels balanced and calm, move to twice-daily use for the full "Nature's Botox" effect.</div>
            <p style="margin-top:16px;"><strong>What to expect:</strong> You may feel a slight warmth — this is the Frankincense increasing circulation. In the first week, skin might purge old impurities as Jojoba clears your pores. After 14 days, redness typically subsides, leaving behind a firm, resilient complexion.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">Is this safe for oily or acne-prone skin?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p>Yes. A common misconception is that oil causes breakouts — in reality, <strong>imbalances</strong> do. We use lightweight, non-comedogenic oils like cold-pressed Jojoba that mimic your skin's natural sebum. This signals your pores to stop overproducing oil, helping to balance and clear your complexion.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">How long does it take to see results?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p>Many users notice an immediate "Ayurvedic glow" and improved hydration after the first few uses. Structural changes — like firmer skin and softened lines — typically unfold over <strong>8 to 12 weeks</strong> of consistent daily ritual.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- CATEGORY 2 -->
    <div class="rv-faq-category">
      <h2 class="rv-faq-category-title">The Ritual — How to Use</h2>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">When should I apply the oil in my routine?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
