    <div class="rv-faq-category">
      <h2 class="rv-faq-category-title">Purity &amp; Ethics</h2>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">Why do you use cold-pressed oils?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p>Heat is the enemy of nutrition. Standard refined oils are processed with high heat and chemicals, which destroys their vitamins and antioxidants. Our cold-pressing method keeps the molecular integrity of the plants intact, ensuring every drop is <em>"living" medicine</em> for your skin.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">Why do you use amber glass bottles?</span>
          <span class="rv-faq-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="rv-faq-answer">
          <div class="rv-faq-answer-inner">
            <p>We choose amber glass for two vital reasons:</p>
            <p><strong>Protection from Light:</strong> The amber tint acts as a natural filter, blocking harmful UV rays that would otherwise oxidize and degrade our delicate cold-pressed oils — keeping nutrients active and powerful for longer.</p>
            <p><strong>Zero Microplastics:</strong> Unlike plastic containers, glass is chemically inert. There is no risk of microplastics or synthetic chemicals leaching into the oil. The purity of our Ayurvedic formula remains 100% untainted from the moment it's bottled until it reaches your skin.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rv-faq-item">
        <button class="rv-faq-question">
          <span class="rv-faq-question-text">Why are there no preservatives?</span>
